Reasoning: The paper discusses recent advances in computer vision and deep learning methods for measuring animal behavior in neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the use of deep learning methods. Additionally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper discusses the potential impact of these tools on real-world neuroscience.
